('18EC53', '', 'Module 1', 'CO  1', 'KL 3', 10, 'With a neat diagram illustrate the major Elements of Communication System</p>\r\n', 'Check the ', '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 2360, 'Block Diagram :3 M</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Elements of Communication System : 3 M</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Working : 4 M</p>\r\n', '<u><strong>Elements of Communication System</strong></u></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Speaker: </strong>&nbsp;the person who begins the communication interaction by having a thought or intended message to send to a listener.<br />\r\n<strong>Encoding &ndash;</strong> the process of creating the message to be transmitted from a sender to the listener. Converting your thoughts and ideas into content that can be transmitted. &nbsp;<strong>Message:</strong> what is actually communicated or transmitted to the listener. &nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Channel: </strong>the means by which the message is communicated. &nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Decoding :</strong>&nbsp;how the listener interprets and processes the message transmitted by the sender. &nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Receiver </strong>:&nbsp;the person or people who receive the speaker&rsquo;s message<br />\r\n<strong>Interference :</strong>&nbsp;anything that could impede the process of communication. (Disturbance /Noise)<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="/svce/ece/qps/ckeditor/kcfinder/upload/images/Q13.jpg" style="height:332px; width:752px" /></p>\r\n', '', '', '1IA'),
('18EC54', '', 'Module 1', 'CO  1', 'KL 2', 10, '<span style="font-size:18px"><span style="font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif">1. A binary sequence is emitting an independent sequence of 0&rsquo;s and 1&rsquo;s with probabilities p and (1-p) respectively. Plot the entropy of the source versus p (0&lt;p&lt;1) [5]</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:18px"><span style="font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif">2.&nbsp;Outline the properties of the entropy with examples [5]</span></span></p>\r\n', 'Y', '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 2361, '<span style="font-size:18px"><span style="font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif">1.&nbsp; Find the entropy of different values of P -3M</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:18px"><span style="font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif">Plot the entropy with P - 2M</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:18px"><span style="font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif">2. List of properties - 3M</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:18px"><span style="font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif">Examples - 2M</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Properties :</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="/svce/ece/qps/ckeditor/kcfinder/upload/images/Plot1.jpg" style="height:816px; width:920px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="/svce/ece/qps/ckeditor/kcfinder/upload/images/Plot2.jpg" style="height:518px; width:622px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Properties :</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="/svce/ece/qps/ckeditor/kcfinder/upload/images/Properties1.jpg" style="height:368px; width:598px" /><img alt="" src="/svce/ece/qps/ckeditor/kcfinder/upload/images/Properties2.jpg" style="height:381px; width:613px" /></p>\r\n', '', '', '1IA'),
