('18EC54', '', 'Module 1', 'CO  1', 'KL 3', 10, '<span style="font-size:18px"><span style="font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif">1. Calculate the entropy of a source that emits one of three symbols A, B and C in a statistically independent sequence with probabilities &nbsp;1/2, 1/4,and 1/4 &nbsp;respectively. [5]</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:18px"><span style="font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif">2.&nbsp;A black and white TV picture consists of 526 lines of picture information assume that each line consists of 526 picture elements (pixels) and that each can have 255 brightness levels. Picture is repeated at the rate of 30 frames per sec. Calculate the average rate of information conveyed by a TV set to a viewer. [5]</span></span></p>\r\n', 'Y', '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 2364, 'Equations - 4M</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Calculation - 6M</p>\r\n', '<img alt="H(s) = sum_{i =1}^{q} Pi log (1/Pi)" src="http://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?H%28s%29%20%3D%20%5Csum_%7Bi%20%3D1%7D%5E%7Bq%7D%20Pi%20log%20%281/Pi%29" />&nbsp;=&nbsp;<span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif">1.5 bits/symbols</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif">2.&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="/svce/ece/qps/ckeditor/kcfinder/upload/images/tv.jpg" /><img alt="" src="/svce/ece/qps/ckeditor/kcfinder/upload/images/tv2.jpg" /></p>\r\n', '', '', '1IA'),
