\r\n<p style="text-align:left"><span style="font-size:14px"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;"><span style="color:black">end</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:left"><span style="font-size:14px"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;"><span style="color:black">// Monitor the outputs</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:left"><span style="font-size:14px"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;"><span style="color:black">initial</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:left"><span style="font-size:14px"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;"><span style="color:black">$monitor($time, &quot; Output q = %d&quot;, q);</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:left"><span style="font-size:14px"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;"><span style="color:black">endmodule</span></span></span></p>\r\n', 'Verilog Code for the above waveform- 10 Marks</p>\r\n', '', '', '1IA'),
('18EC53', '', 'Module 2', 'CO  2', 'KL 3', 10, 'Illustrate the generation of Wideband frequency modulated wave using the direct method</p>\r\n', 'Y', '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 2403, '', 'It is a process of altering Frequency of carrier signal in accordance with instantaneous values of message signal by keeping Amplitude, phase of Carrier constant. The General Equation of FM Signal is given by</p>\r\n\r\n<p>=&nbsp;&nbsp;cos2&nbsp;+2&nbsp;()S(t)= A_C&nbsp;&nbsp; cos[2&pi; f_c t+2&pi; K_P &int;1m(t)t]</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Where _ = Phase Sensitivity parameter.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;() = Message Signal<br />\r\nExplain..</p>\r\n', '', '', '1IA'),
