shes the limits of sampling in both directions. Quantization of the sensor outputs is as before. Figure 2.6 illustrates this concept. Figure 2.6(a) shows a continuous image projected onto the plane of an array sensor. Figure 2.6(b) shows the image after sampling and quantization. Clearly, the quality of a digital image is determined to a large degree by the number of samples and discrete intensity levels used in sampling and quantization. However, as we show in Section 2.4.3, image content is also an important consideration in choosing these parameters.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n', '', '', 'IA 2');
