erif&quot;">is in N</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">4</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">(p),<em> or</em></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm"><span style="font-size:10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;"><strong><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">(ii)</span></span></strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">q </span></span></em><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">is in N</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">D</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">(p)<em> and </em>the set N</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">4</span></span></sub><em> </em><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">(p)&cap;N</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">4</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">(q)</span></span>&nbsp; <span style="font-size:11.5pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">has no pixels whose values are from <em>V</em>.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">Mixed adjacency is a modification of 8-adjacency. It is introduced to eliminate the ambiguities that often arise when 8-adjacency is used. </span></span></p>\r\n', '', '', 'IA 2');
INSERT INTO `question_master2` (`course_code`, `CID`, `mo`, `co`, `kl`, `marks`, `question`, `r1`, `remarks1`, `r2`, `remarks2`, `r3`, `remarks3`, `final`, `q_id`, `question_number`, `qno`, `key1`, `scheme`, `cat2`, `ete`, `IA`) VALUES
('15EC72', '', 'Module 1', 'CO  1', 'KL 3', 10, '<p>illustrate linear and non linear operations in details</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Y', '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 2938, 'Linear operations-5M</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Non linear operations-5M</p>\r\n', '<span style="font-size:10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">One of the most important classifications of an image-processing method is whether it is linear or nonlinear. Consider a general operator, <em>H</em>, that produces an output image, <em>g</em>(<em>x</em>, <em>y</em>), for a given input image, <em>f</em> (<em>x</em>, <em>y</em>): H[f(x, y)] = g(x, y) &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;2.4.4</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm"><span style="font-size:10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;"><em><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">H </span></span></em><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">is said to be a<em> linear operator </em>if</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm"><span style="font-size:10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">H[a</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">i</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> f</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">i</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> (x, y) + a</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">j</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> f</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">j</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> (x, y) ] = a</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">i</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> H[f</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">i</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> (x, y) ] + a</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">j</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> H[f</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">j</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> (x, y) ] = a</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">i</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> g</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">i</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> (x, y) + a</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">j</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> g</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">j</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> (x, y)&hellip;&hellip;2.4.5</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm; text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">where a</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">i</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">, a</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">j</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">, f</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">i</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">(x, y) and f</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">j</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">(x, y) are arbitrary constants and images (of the same size), respectively.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm; text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">Equation (2.4.5) indicates that the output of a linear operation due to the sum of two inputs is the same as performing the operation on the inputs individually and then summing the results. In addition, the output of a linear operation to a constant time an input is the same as the output of the operation due to the original input multiplied by that constant. The first property is called the property of <strong><em>additivity</em></strong> and the second is called the property of <strong><em>homogeneity</em>.</strong></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm; text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">As a simple example, suppose that <em>H</em> is the sum operator, &sum;; that is, the function of this operator is simply to sum its inputs. To test for linearity, we start with the left side of Eq. (2.4.5) and attempt to prove that it is equal to the right side:</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="font-size:10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">[a</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">i</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">f</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">i</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> (x, y) + a</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">j</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> f</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">j</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> (x, y) ] = &sum; a</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">i</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> f</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">i</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> (x, y) + &sum;a</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">j</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> f</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">j</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> (x, y)&hellip;2.4.6</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style="list-style-type:none">\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li><span style="font-size:10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">a</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">i</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">&sum;fi (x, y) + a</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">j</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">&sum;f</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">j</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> (x, y)</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style="list-style-type:none">\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li><span style="font-size:10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">a</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">i</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> g</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">i</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> (x, y) + a</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">j</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> g</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">j</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> (x, y)</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm; text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">where the first step follows from the fact that summation is distributive. So, an expansion of the left side is equal to the right side of Eq. (2.4.5), and we conclude that the sum operator is linear.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm"><span style="font-size:10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;"><strong><span style="font-size:14.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">1.13 SUMMARY</span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm; text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">The main purpose of the unit is to provide a sense of perspective about the origins of digital image processing and also about current and future areas of application of this technology. Upon concluding the study of the chapter, a reader will have arrived at a level of understanding that is the foundation for most of the work currently underway in this field. Also the material in this unit is primarily background for subsequent discussions. The treatment of the human visual system provides a basic idea of the capabilities of the eye in perceiving pictorial information. The image model developed is used as the basis for an image enhancement technique called <em>homomorphic filtering</em>. The sampling and interpolation ideas introduced for the foundation for many of the digitizing phenomena. The concepts introduced in this section are the basic building blocks for processing techniques based on pixel neighborhoods. Also mentioned in that section, the tools introduced. A comprehensive treatment of mathematical concepts introduced, it considerably more meaningful to learn the necessary extensions of the mathematical tools in the context of how they are applied to solve problems in image processing.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n', '', '', 'IA 2'),
('17EC72', '', 'Module 1', 'CO  1', 'KL 3', 10, '<p>Illustrate linear and non linear operations in details</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Y', '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 2939, 'Linear operations-5M</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Non linear operations-5M</p>\r\n', '<span style="font-size:10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">One of the most important classifications of an image-processing method is whether it is linear or nonlinear. Consider a general operator, <em>H</em>, that produces an output image, <em>g</em>(<em>x</em>, <em>y</em>), for a given input image, <em>f</em> (<em>x</em>, <em>y</em>): H[f(x, y)] = g(x, y) &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;2.4.4</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm"><span style="font-size:10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;"><em><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">H </span></span></em><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">is said to be a<em> linear operator </em>if</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm"><span style="font-size:10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">H[a</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">i</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> f</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">i</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> (x, y) + a</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">j</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> f</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">j</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> (x, y) ] = a</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">i</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> H[f</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">i</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> (x, y) ] + a</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">j</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> H[f</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">j</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> (x, y) ] = a</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">i</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> g</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">i</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> (x, y) + a</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">j</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> g</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">j</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> (x, y)&hellip;&hellip;2.4.5</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm; text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">where a</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">i</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">, a</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">j</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">, f</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">i</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">(x, y) and f</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">j</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">(x, y) are arbitrary constants and images (of the same size), respectively.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm; text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">Equation (2.4.5) indicates that the output of a linear operation due to the sum of two inputs is the same as performing the operation on the inputs individually and then summing the results. In addition, the output of a linear operation to a constant time an input is the same as the output of the operation due to the original input multiplied by that constant. The first property is called the property of <strong><em>additivity</em></strong> and the second is called the property of <strong><em>homogeneity</em>.</strong></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm; text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">As a simple example, suppose that <em>H</em> is the sum operator, &sum;; that is, the function of this operator is simply to sum its inputs. To test for linearity, we start with the left side of Eq. (2.4.5) and attempt to prove that it is equal to the right side:</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="font-size:10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">[a</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">i</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">f</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">i</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> (x, y) + a</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">j</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> f</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">j</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> (x, y) ] = &sum; a</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">i</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> f</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">i</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> (x, y) + &sum;a</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">j</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> f</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">j</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> (x, y)&hellip;2.4.6</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style="list-style-type:none">\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li><span style="font-size:10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">a</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">i</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">&sum;fi (x, y) + a</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">j</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">&sum;f</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">j</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> (x, y)</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style="list-style-type:none">\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li><span style="font-size:10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">a</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">i</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> g</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">i</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> (x, y) + a</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">j</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> g</span></span><sub><span style="font-size:16.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">j</span></span></sub><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"> (x, y)</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm; text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">where the first step follows from the fact that summation is distributive. So, an expansion of the left side is equal to the right side of Eq. (2.4.5), and we conclude that the sum operator is linear.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm"><span style="font-size:10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;"><strong><span style="font-size:14.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">1.13 SUMMARY</span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm; text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">The main purpose of the unit is to provide a sense of perspective about the origins of digital image processing and also about current and future areas of application of this tec