('18EC52', '', 'Module 3', 'CO  3', 'KL 3', 10, '<span style="font-size:12px"><span style="font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif">The impulse response of the FIR filter is given by h(n) = {1, -2, 3}, for the input&nbsp;&nbsp;x(n) = { 6, -2, 3, -2, 3, 9, 4, 6, 7, 8, 0, -1} &nbsp;calculate the y(n), using overlap Add method and 6- Circular convolution.</span></span><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Y', '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 2992, 'Step-1: 2 Marks<br />\r\nStep-2: 2 Marks<br />\r\nStep-3: 2 Marks<br />\r\nStep-4: 2 Marks<br />\r\nStep-5: 2 Marks<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', '', '', 'IA 2'),
