('18EC52', '', 'Module 3', 'CO  3', 'KL 2', 10, '<span style="font-size:12px"><span style="font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif">&nbsp;Determine x(n)*h(n) for x(n) and h(n) given below using Overlap Add method using DFT-IDFT method. h(n) = {1,3, -3}, x(n) = { 1, 2, 1, 1, -3, 0 , -3, -2, 3, 2, &nbsp;4, 2, -1}.</span></span></p>\r\n', 'Y', '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 2995, 'Step-1: 2 Marks<br />\r\nStep-2: 2 Marks<br />\r\nStep-3: 2 Marks<br />\r\nStep-4: 2 Marks<br />\r\nStep-5: 2 Marks<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', '', '', 'IA 2'),
('15EC71', '', 'Module 2', 'CO  2', 'KL 4', 10, '<p style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:12px"><span style="font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif">Given [z]=&nbsp;<img alt="egin{bmatrix} 3&amp;7  2&amp;5 end{bmatrix}" src="http://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?%5Cbegin%7Bbmatrix%7D%203%267%20%5C%5C%202%265%20%5Cend%7Bbmatrix%7D" />. Find S-matrix.&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n', 'Y', '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 2996, '', '', '', '', 'IA 2'),
('18EC36', '', 'Module 2', 'CO  2', 'KL 4', 10, '<span style="font-size:12px"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">Construct and illustrate the Step-Up Chopper circuit operations with RL Load. Derive an expression for output voltage or load voltage of the same.</span></span></p>\r\n', 'Y', '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 2997, 'Circuit Diagram - 2M</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Waveforms - 3M</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Explnation&nbsp; - 5M</p>\r\n', '<img alt="" src="/svce/ece/qps/ckeditor/kcfinder/upload/images/StepUP%20Chopper%20with%20RL%20Load.jpg" style="height:227px; width:492px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:12px"><span style="font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif">The values of L and C are chosen depending upon the&nbsp;requirement of output voltage and current.<br />\r\n&bull; When the chopper is ON, the inductor L is connected across&nbsp;the supply.<br />\r\n&bull; The inductor current &lsquo;I&rsquo; rises and the inductor stores energy&nbsp;during the ON time of the chopper, tON.<br />\r\n&bull; When the chopper is off, the inductor current I is forced to flow&nbsp;through the diode D and load for a period, toff.<br />\r\n&bull; The current tends to decrease resulting in reversing the polarity&nbsp;of induced EMF in L.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:12px"><span style="font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif">Voltage across load is given by: Vo = Vdc + L (di/dt)</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:12px"><span style="font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif">If a large capacitor &lsquo;C&rsquo; is connected across the load&nbsp;then the capacitor will provide a continuous output&nbsp;voltage .<br />\r\n&bull; Diode D prevents any current flow from capacitor to&nbsp;the source.<br />\r\n&bull; Step up choppers are used for regenerative braking of&nbsp;dc motors.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:12px"><span style="font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif">Assume the average inductor current to be I during&nbsp;ON and OFF time of Chopper.<br />\r\nWhen Chopper is ON<br />\r\n&bull; Voltage across inductor L = Vdc<br />\r\n&bull; Therefore energy stored in an inductor = V.I.t<sub>on</sub><br />\r\nWhen Chopper is OFF (energy is supplied by inductor&nbsp;to load)<br />\r\n&bull; Voltage across L = V<sub>o</sub>- V<sub>dc</sub><br />\r\n&bull; Energy supplied by inductor L =&nbsp;(V<sub>o</sub> - V<sub>dc</sub>).I.t<sub>off</sub><br />\r\n&bull; Neglecting losses, energy stored in inductor L =&nbsp;energy supplied by inductor L :&nbsp;V.I.t<sub>on </sub>= (V<sub>o</sub> - V<sub>dc</sub>).I.t<sub>off</sub></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:12px"><span style="font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif">V<sub>o</sub> = V<sub>dc</sub> [&nbsp;t<sub>on&nbsp;</sub>+&nbsp;t<sub>off</sub>] /&nbsp;t<sub>off </sub>=<sub>&nbsp;</sub>V<sub>dc</sub> . T / [T - t<sub>on</sub>] =&nbsp;V<sub>dc</sub> .[1/(1-t<sub>on/</sub>T)] =&nbsp;V<sub>dc</sub> .[1/(1-d)]</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:12px"><span style="font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif">Note: the variation of&nbsp;duty cycle &lsquo;d&rsquo; in the range of 0&lt;d&lt;1 the output&nbsp;voltage will vary in the range of V&lt;output voltage&lt;infinity.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', '', 'IA 2'),
('15EC71', '', 'Module 2', 'CO  2', 'KL 4', 10, '<p style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-size:12px"><span style="font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif">State the properties of S-parameters, prove the symmetry property and unitary property of S-parameter.</span></span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n', 'Y', '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 2998, '', '<p><input alt="" src="/svce/ece/qps11/ckeditor/kcfinder/upload/files/properties%20of%20S-matrix%283%29.jpg" style="width: 2024px; height: 2212px;" type="image" /></p>\r\n', '', '', 'IA 2');
