('18EC36', '', 'Module 3', 'CO  3', 'KL 1', 10, '<span style="font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif"><span style="font-size:12px">a)&nbsp;Define an Inverter? With neat hierarchical chart briefly explain different classifications of inverters</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif"><span style="font-size:12px">b)&nbsp;Distinguish between Voltage Source Inverters and Current Source Inverters.</span></span></p>\r\n', 'Y', '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 3002, 'a) Definition of Inverter Circuit - 2M</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Classification of inverters with hirarchical chart - 4M</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b) various parametric differences between VSI and CSI Inverters - 4M</p>\r\n', '<span style="font-size:12px"><span style="font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif">A static device that converts DC power into AC&nbsp; power at desired output voltage and frequency is&nbsp;called an Inverter.<br />\r\n&bull; Applications of inverters<br />\r\n&ndash; Adjustable &ndash; speed AC drives,&nbsp;&ndash; Induction Heating,&nbsp;&ndash; Aircraft power supplies,&nbsp;&ndash; UPS etc&hellip;.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:12px"><span style="font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif">Classification of Inverters<br />\r\n&bull; According to the method of Commutation<br />\r\n&ndash; Line Commutated Inverter<br />\r\n&ndash; Force Commutated Inverter<br />\r\n&bull; According to the method of Connections<br />\r\n&ndash;Series Inverter<br />\r\n&ndash;Parallel Inverter<br />\r\n&ndash;Bridge Type Inverter<br />\r\n&bull; According to the nature of DC source feeding the<br />\r\nInverter<br />\r\n&ndash; Voltage source Inverter<br />\r\n&ndash; Current Source Inverter</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:12px"><span style="font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif">b)&nbsp;Voltage Source Inverters<br />\r\n&bull; VSI has a constant voltage at its input terminals.<br />\r\n&bull; Its output voltage does not depend on load.<br />\r\n&bull; Its output current depends on the type of load.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:12px"><span style="font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif">Voltage Source Inverters<br />\r\n&bull; Single phase Inverter<br />\r\n&bull; Half Bridge Inverter<br />\r\n&bull; Full Bridge Inverter<br />\r\n&bull; Three phase voltage source inverter<br />\r\n&bull; 180 degree mode<br />\r\n&bull; 120 degree mode</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:12px"><span style="font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif">Current Source Inverters<br />\r\n&bull; CSI has a constant current at its input terminals.<br />\r\n&bull; Its output current does not depend on load.<br />\r\n&bull; Its output voltage depends on the type of load.</span></span></p>\r\n', '', '', 'IA 2'),
