('18EC72', '', 'Module 4', 'CO  4', 'KL 2', 10, '<span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">Explain Max-delay constraints with neat logic diagram and waveform.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n', 'Y', '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 3014, 'Logic diagram of Max-delay constraints.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Explaination</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Waveform</p>\r\n', '<img alt="" src="/svce/ece/qps/ckeditor/kcfinder/upload/images/s1.PNG" style="height:269px; width:520px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="/svce/ece/qps/ckeditor/kcfinder/upload/images/s2.PNG" style="height:385px; width:566px" /></p>\r\n', '', '', 'IA 2'),
('18EC36', '', 'Module 3', 'CO  3', 'KL 4', 10, '<span style="font-size:12px"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">By applying appropriate input voltage determine the operating procedure of discontinuous mode isolated fly-back converter in different operating modes</span></span></p>\r\n', 'Y', '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 3015, 'Circuit diagram - 2M</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Differet Modes of operations with Circuit Diagrams - 6M</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Waveforms - 2M&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<img alt="" src="/svce/ece/qps/ckeditor/kcfinder/upload/images/Dicontinuous%20Converter.jpg" style="float:left; height:283px; width:501px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif"><span style="font-size:12px">Fly-back converter is the most commonly used&nbsp;SMPS circuit<br />\r\n&bull; Low output power applications<br />\r\n&bull; The output voltage needs to be isolated from&nbsp;the input main supply<br />\r\n&bull; The output power may vary from few watts to&nbsp;less than 100 watts.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif"><span style="font-size:12px">The circuit can offer single or multiple isolated&nbsp;output voltages<br />\r\n&bull; Operate over wide range of input voltage&nbsp;variation.<br />\r\n&bull; In respect of energy-efficiency, fly-back power&nbsp;supplies are inferior to many other SMPS&nbsp;circuits but its simple topology and low cost&nbsp;makes it popular in low output power range.&nbsp;Typical efficiency of a fly-back converter is&nbsp;around 65%-75%.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif"><span style="font-size:12px">When switch &lsquo;S&rsquo; is on, the primary winding of the transformer gets&nbsp;connected to the input supply with its dotted end connected to the&nbsp;positive side.<br />\r\nAt this time the diode &lsquo;D&rsquo; connected in series with the secondary&nbsp;winding gets reverse biased due to the induced voltage in the&nbsp;secondary (dotted end potential being higher).&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif"><span style="font-size:12px">Mode 1: Switch is ON; Diode is OFF;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif"><span style="font-size:12px">E<sub>dc</sub> = L<sub>p</sub> .&nbsp;(di / dt)</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif"><span style="font-size:12px">At the end of Mode-1, energy stored in the primary winding is&nbsp; = L<sub>p</sub> . I<sub>p</sub><sup>2</sup> / 2</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif"><span style="font-size:12px">Mode 2: Switch is OFF, Diode is ON<br />\r\nWhen Switch turns off, the current in the primary&nbsp;winding drops suddenly, the voltage across the&nbsp;primary winding reverses.&nbsp;The diode becomes forward biased.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif"><span style="font-size:12px">Mode-3:&nbsp;During discontinuous mode, MOSFET is OFF; Diode is OFF.&nbsp;The output capacitor continues to supply uninterrupted voltage to the load.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif"><span style="font-size:12px">Flyback Applications<br />\r\n&bull; Usually low-cost, low-power (&lt;100W)<br />\r\n&bull; Low-cost as no output inductor and cheap&nbsp;output diode (DCM)<br />\r\nDisadvantages<br />\r\n&bull; Output spike at turn-off (due to ESR)<br />\r\n&bull; Large filter capacitor and ripple current rating</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="/svce/ece/qps/ckeditor/kcfinder/upload/images/Dicontinuous%20Converter%20Modes.jpg" style="float:left; height:284px; width:1366px" /></p>\r\n', '', '', 'IA 2'),
